OL,6,FMr Childs lay undiscovered as Harkin
OL,7,Fwent to the prison's showers and
OL,8,Fassaulted another prisoner - his
OL,9,Fprevious cellmate - with a makeshift
OL,10,Fblade.
OL,12,FThe court heard this prisoner had
OL,13,Frequested to no longer share a room
OL,14,Fwith Harkin just days prior, saying
OL,15,Fthere "was something not right about"
OL,16,Fhim. He suffered wounds to his face,
OL,17,Fshoulder, neck, arms and leg in the
OL,18,Fassault.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
